  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health and Economic Livelihoods Partnership (HELP) and Building Alliances in Support of Cooperative Development Objectives: The EUCLID Alliance (CDP IV)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HELP is a collaborative effort between NCBA CLUSA, Health Partners, and WOCCU. Together, the consortium of cooperative development partners bring sector specific expertise to help tackle the development challenges facing Haiti. The HELP team is developing a comprehensive program design methodology and suggested programming to begin to address these challenges. 
The EUCLID Alliance program strengthens alliances between US and overseas cooperatives and assists USAID and CDOs to design better cooperative programs. This program improves service provision to members and engages in trade which will provide tangible member benefits and contribute to more jobs and higher incomes, greater food security, stronger purchasing power and sustainable economic growth through the pilot programs in Latin America and Indonesia.  NCBA CLUSA has organized an alliance of cooperatives that works together on this project through an innovative platform. This alliance includes cooperative market actors in the US and overseas, cooperative finance actors, technical assistance actors and an organization specializing in cooperative metrics.
Other activities under EUCLID alliance include:
Reviewing existing case studies and lessons learned, developed by NCBA CLUSA and other CDOs; holding workshops involving key cooperative experts to discuss business models and framework for alliance building; developing guide/manual for coop alliance building; sharing lessons learned from coop to coop trade with the International Cooperative Alliance; facilitating the exchange of samples from pilot countries; exploring strategies for best use of grants under CDP Alliances award; attending trade conferences to build trade relationships; forming additional strategic partnerships with key commodity companies to leverage supply chain contacts; increasing awareness and educating cooperative consumers at US grocery trade fairs; facilitating cooperative trade exposure visits to pilot locations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through USAID&apos;s Cooperative Development Program (CDP), NCBA CLUSA works to strengthen the capacity of local organizations to carry out activities that build and strengthen cooperative systems in their own countries in order to improve their quality of life. CDP IV supports development and expansion of economic assistance programs that utilize cooperatives and credit unions and includes two main technical components: Health and Economic Livelihoods Partnership (HELP) in Haiti and Building Alliances in Support of Cooperative Development in Latin America and Indonesia through the EUCLID Alliance.</narrative>
  </description>
